choices.text:
Put together a healthy meal plan for me for 7 days.  I can't have dairy, garlic, honey, almonds, or cashews
Here is your personalized menu, please let me know if you would like any changes. You will need to prepare the following meals in advance and store them appropriately so that they are ready when needed : 
 - Day 1 (Monday): Chicken breast with steamed broccoli 
-Day 2 (Tuesday) : Salmon fillet with roasted asparagus, sweet potato wedges, green beans  and a side salad of spinach leaves.   
-Day 3( Wednesday ): Beef stew and baked potatoes. You can prepare the beef stock in advance to save time on this day 
 - Day 4: Turkey meatballs served over spaghetti squash with steamed broccoli 
- Day 5 (Thursday): Chicken breast, roasted sweet potato wedges, green beans  and a side salad of spinach leaves.   
-Day 6( Friday ): Salmon fillet and baked potatoes. You can prepare the salmon in advance to save time on this day 
 - Day 7: Beef stew served over spaghetti squash with steamed broccoli
